        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 3:29AM CDT by NWS Hastings NE</headline>
        <description>At 328 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Deshler, or 18 miles north of Belleville, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Deshler, Chester, Byron, Hubbell and rural southwest Thayer County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
